Trench 57, 1998, Loci 27, 28, 29, 31 (i.e., channelization), Trench 57, 1998, Locus 20 (South Wall and “Door”), Trench 85, 2001, Locus 22 (Channel System).

The north south channelization possibly was a later addition to the water systems in the Central Arch. Although Trench 57, 1998, Locus 20 (South Wall) completely bars further investigation. The excavator believes that the original water system possibly was just this cut that led directly into the central canalization.
